# Room CRUD Admin Interface

Build a full Room management page in the Angular admin panel. Admins can view, create, edit, and delete Rooms. The backend `/api/rooms` endpoints will be restricted to `ADMIN` role only.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend

#### [MODIFY] [SecurityConfig.java](file:///c:/PI%20AMMAR/Esprit-PiProject-4SAE8-2026-CertifyPro/backend/services/user-service/src/main/java/com/training/platform/security/SecurityConfig.java)
- Add rule: `POST`, `PUT`, `DELETE` on `/api/rooms/**` → restricted to `ROLE_ADMIN`.
- `GET /api/rooms/**` → any authenticated user (so trainers can pick rooms when creating sessions later).

#### [MODIFY] [RoomController.java](file:///c:/PI%20AMMAR/Esprit-PiProject-4SAE8-2026-CertifyPro/backend/services/user-service/src/main/java/com/training/platform/controller/RoomController.java)
- Add `@CrossOrigin` awareness (already handled by global CORS). No changes needed unless specific annotations needed.

---

### Frontend

#### [MODIFY] [api.config.ts](file:///c:/PI%20AMMAR/Esprit-PiProject-4SAE8-2026-CertifyPro/frontend/src/app/core/api/api.config.ts)
- Add `rooms` endpoint to `API_ENDPOINTS`.

#### [NEW] `features/rooms/services/rooms.api.ts`
